<1ST_LINE>u a AM-MurderVideoTrial     11-26 0162</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Murder Video Trial,0165</2ND_LINE>
<BYLINE>URGENT</BYLINE>
<HEAD>Jury Convicts `Murder Video' Defendant Of Killing Daughter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ELIZABETH CITY, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who assumed multiple
personalities under hypnosis while on trial for the slaying of his
19-year-old daughter was convicted Friday of first-degree murder.
   Thomas Lee Bonney pleaded innocent by reason of insanity in the
death of Kathy Carol Bonney, whose nude body was shot 27 times and
dumped last November at the Dismal Swamp Canal, just inside North
Carolina's border with Virginia.
   Bonney, 45, of Chesapeake, Va., revealed the personas of
``Satan,'' his dead grandmother and three other of his 10
personalities in videotaped interviews with Dr. Paul F. Dell, a
psyuchiatrist retained by the defense.
   ``You're just a mortal,'' Bonney growled during one session under
hypnosis with Dell, a professor at Norfolk's Eastern Virginia
Medical School. ``You don't know nothing.''
   
   The jury began deliberations at late Friday afternoon after
hearing six hours of closing arguments and three weeks of testimony.
</TEXT>
