<1ST_LINE>r i PM-BRF--Hungary-Albania     11-26 0141</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Hungary-Albania,0146</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hungary To Exchange Ambassadors With Albania</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hungary has agreed to exchange
ambassadors with Albania for the first time since Albania and the
Soviet bloc scaled back diplomatic ties in the 1960s, Hungary's
official news agency said.
   The MTI agency made the announcement Friday in a one-sentence
report.
   Albania agreed in May to exchange ambassadors with East Germany
and in August to exchange ambassadors with Bulgaria.
   In New York for the U.N. General Assembly last month, Albanian
Foreign Minister Reis Malile met his counterparts from Hungary,
Czechoslovakia, Bulgaria, East Germany, Poland and China.
   The Albanian rapprochement with the Soviet bloc has occurred
without any apparent change of attitude to the Soviet Union, with
which Albania severed all ties in 1961.
   Albania has had ties on the charge d'affaires level with most
other Soviet bloc nations.
</TEXT>
