<HEAD>Priest Shot and Killed, Moslem Fundamentalists Suspected</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ASSIUT, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 32-year-old Coptic priest was shot and
killed by masked gunmen believed to be Moslem fundamentalists,
authorities say.
   A security source said on condition of anonymity that the
shooting took place Thursday night as the priest left his church, 25
miles south of Assiut, for home.
   He said the priest previously clashed with Moslem fundamentalists
in the village. He said the extremists had asked the priest to limit
his gatherings and activities in the church to Sundays, but that he
refused.
   The source said two or three masked gunmen ambushed the priest
and shot him several times in the head. He was moved to a hospital
but died there. He was buried in a funeral Friday under heavy
security.
   The source said that Interior Minister Zaki Badr has ordered an
investigation.
</TEXT>
