<HEAD>Current Quotations</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   ``There's stroller gridlock in places.'' _ Susan Inskeep, with
her grandson at a mall in suburban Los Angeles, commenting on the
crush of people during the usual post-Thanksgiving rush of Christmas
shopping.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``The Bard is made of strong stuff, so he would probably laugh
out of wry amusement at this. In my view, people would be far better
off reading his work.'' _ Anne Barton, a Cambridge University
English professor, deriding the moot court being held in London on
whether William Shakespeare wrote the plays and poems attributed to
him, or Edward de Vere, the 17th Earl of Oxford.
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
   ``I was sitting watching TV and all at once I started feeling
dizzy. I thought there was something wrong with me, then I realized
everything was shaking.'' _ Roy Tabikha of Cambridge, Mass.,
recounting his reaction to the strong eastern Canada earthquake that
also shook the northeastern United States.
