<1ST_LINE>r a PM-MurderVideo     11-26 0288</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Murder Video,0295</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Found Guilty In Shooting Death Of Daughter</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ELIZABETH CITY, N.C. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who a psychologist testified
has multiple personalities has been found guilty of first-degree
murder in the shooting death of his 19-year-old daughter a year ago.
   A Camden County jury returned its verdict against Thomas Lee
Bonney on Friday. His daughter, Kathy Carol Bonney was found dead
last November along the Dismal Swamp Canal, just south of the North
Carolina-Virginia border.
   Bonney, 45, of Chesapeake, Va., pleaded innocent by reason of
insanity, saying he suffered from a multiple personality disorder
and that one of his nine other personalities was in control at the
time of the shooting.
   Bonney revealed the personas of ``Satan,'' his dead grandmother
and three other of his 10 personalities in videotaped interviews
with Dr. Paul F. Dell, a psyuchiatrist retained by the defense.
   ``You're just a mortal,'' Bonney growled during one session under
hypnosis with Dell, a professor at Norfolk's Eastern Virginia
Medical School. ``You don't know nothing.''
   The jury will return Monday to consider whether Bonney should
receive the death penalty or life imprisonment.
   ``I'm pleased with the jury's verdict,'' District Attorney H.P.
Williams said. ``It shows we did our work, although we've got a lot
more work to do before next week's hearing.''
   Bonney's court-appointed defense attorneys left the courthouse
without comment.
   Williams had argued that Bonney deliberately killed his daughter
out of a possessive anger over her relationship with a married man.
   Hours before the verdict was announced, Bonney tried to escape
while deputies were taking him to the jail. Bonney jumped from the
car and fled about 50 feet before he was grabbed by the deputies,
said Pasquotank County Sheriff Davis Sawyer.
</TEXT>
