<2ND_LINE>PM-Fire Deaths,0201</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Four Dead, One Injured In House Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MINNEAPOLIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Four people were killed and a fifth was
critically injured early today in a house fire, officials said.
   Killed were a woman, believed to be in her early 40s, her two
sons, ages 12 and 22, and a visitor, a 21-year-old man, said Gary
Kaldun, a Hennepin County medical examiner's investigator. Another
visitor, the 21-year-old man's twin brother, was critically injured.
   Names were being withheld pending notification of relatives.
   The two young men were pronounced dead at the scene, Kaldun said.
The 12-year-old boy was dead on arrival at Hennepin County Medical
Center and his mother died after arriving at the hospital, an
emergency room nurse said.
   The woman and child appeared to have died from smoke inhalation,
said the nurse, who declined to be identified. She said doctors were
working on the fifth person in the emergency room.
   The fire at the two-story, wood-frame duplex, which is two blocks
from a fire station, was reported about 4:30 a.m. and brought under
control within an hour.
   The second floor, where the victims were found, was gutted and
the stairway charred.
</TEXT>
