<HEAD>Five Injured In Hospital Fire</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A fire broke out Saturday at Hadassah Hospital
and five policemen and firefighters who evacuated the patients were
injured, authorities said.
   No injuries were reported among the patients.
   Police spokesman Rafi Levy and Hadassah officials said the fire
broke out at the hospital's laundry. The smoke spread through
ventilation openings and engulfed three floors, they said.
   Fire brigades and emergency medical and police teams evacuated
patients stationed at the damaged floors, fire brigade chief Pinchas
Suhami said.
   The radio said two police officers and a firefighters were
injured by smoke inhalation and two other firefighters by broken
glass.
   The cause was under investigation.
