<HEAD>URGENT</HEAD>
<HEAD>U.S. Denies PLO Leader Visa To Visit U.N.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The State Department said Saturday it has
rejected Palestine Liberation Oraganization chairman Yasser Arafat's
visa application to visit the United States to address the United
Nations.
   Secretary of State George Shultz released his decision in a
two-page statement given to reporters.
   The PLO applied for a visa so Arafat could travel to New York to
address the United Nations on Dec. 1 when it opens its debate on the
Palestine questions.
