<HEAD>Five Die in Ammunition Blast</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BUENOS AIRES, Argentina (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A load of ammunition slated to be
dismantled at military depot exploded Saturday, killing four
soldiers and one civilian in a southeastern town, officials said.
   Army Lt. Col. Jorge Jesus Ezcurra, commander of the 602nd arsenal
batallion, said in a statement that the explosion occurred near the
town of Pigue, 450 kilometers southeast of Buenos Aires.
   The cause of the accident was unclear, but the Army indicated the
explosion occurred in a truck that was being used to transport the
munitions.
   Pieces of shrapnel and munitions casings were scattered over a
wide area and guards were posted to prevent further accidents, the
Army said.
   The batallion, in charge of the ammunition dump, stored
explosives that were to be dismantled.
   The dead included a first lieutenant, three corporals and an Army
civilian employee.
</TEXT>
